Interface JsonFieldDeserializer<T>

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    ListChildrenResponseDeserializer.ListChildrenResponseFieldDeserializer, MoveNodeToTrashResponseDeserializer.MoveNodeToTrashResponseFieldDeserializer, NodeDeserializer.NodeFieldDeserializer, PaginatedCloudDriveResponseFieldDeserializer

    public interface JsonFieldDeserializer<T>
    Defines how to read a JsonParser at a given field to be set on a value.

    • Method Detail

      • handleField

        <U extends T> boolean handleField(JsonParser parser,
                                java.lang.String fieldName,
                                U value)
                    throws java.io.IOException
        Called when a new field name is read from the parser. This defines how to deserialize the field and set it on the value and returns that it was handled, or defines that the field should be skipped.
        Type Parameters:
        U - The type of the value which is being mutated based on the deserialization and is a sub-type of T.
        Parameters:
        parser - The parser of a given InputStream.
        fieldName - The current field name that marks the parser current position.
        value - The instance which will be mutated based on the how the current field is handled.
        Returns:
        true if the fieldName was used to mutate the value; otherwise false.
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException - An error occurred while deserializing the fieldName from the parser.
